FBIS4-17926 "drsov082_a_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-082 Daily Report 26 Apr 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Yeltsin Recommends Talks on Joint Exercises Yeltsin Recommends Talks on Joint Exercises LD2604113794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1124 GMT 26 Apr 94 LD2604113794 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] [Text] Moscow April 26 TASS -- Boris Yeltsin regards "with understanding" the doubts expressed in the State Duma, the lower house of the Russian parliament, about the advisability of the first-ever Russian-U.S. staff exercises which were planned to be held in the Orenburg region. The president recommended that the Defence Ministry hold additional consultations with the U.S. side and consider the matter again "with due regard for both the stance of the Russian lawmakers and comments made in this connection by the general public," the presidential press service announced.
